Use the standard library
This is how to has_close_elements of numbers and threshold:
   Remember that n is numbers's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that j is sum of i and 1
      Do this diff of n and j times:
         Remember that diff_val is abs of (diff of item i in numbers and item j in numbers)
         When diff_val is less than threshold, then:
            The answer is 1
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is 0
